use a descriptive file to describe clips

here's the types and their properties

image: start, duration, (audio)

text: start, text[],position[],fontsize[], audio/duration, bg_img, bg_color, 

video: start, file

color: color, duration/audio

audio: start, file



use a descriptive file to describe screens:
and it can generate clips.json as defined before
here's the types of their properties:

image: duration, audio, 

text: duration, audio, mode, padding

blank: color or transparent, duration, audio, 

bgm
